	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There was some piece of software—I don't know what—that makes very tidy looking schematics in 1bpp bitmaps. Enri used it when he made schematics of the famicom and peripherals: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://atariusa.com/Famicom_Schematics/">http://atariusa.com/Famicom_Schematics/</a><!-- m --><br />They usually provide a much more dense image than a standard schematic, and resultantly are smaller and so use less memory and so work better on less capable computers.<br /><br />That said, I can't think of a non-awful way to convert an existing schematic in this way. Maybe some trick with the PDF to force it to use a nice bitmap font as part of the export process.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


